Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Name: Mummy breast cover
Description: Trapezoid-shaped mummy breast cover with from top to bottom: a winged solar disc flanked by two falcon heads; a wesekh-collar; Nephthys, Osiris and Isis all mummiform, crouched and facing right. The small size recalls the mummy of a child. Beige background.
